album.title: Best of Blind Willie McTell: Classic Recordings of the 1920's & 30's

track.name: Statesboro Blues
comments: This is what it's all about!
Turn your lamp down low and listen to this marvellous track
"I looked over in the corner, Grandma' and Grandpa' had 'em too..."
Actually the Allman Brothers version is based on Taj Mahal's cover of this song.
So this is where the Allman Brothers got this one from...very nice.
one of his best.i like the pick up midway through.
"Treated me like a King and she was a dog-gone Queen"
Broke Down Engine is one of his best
Every time I hear this song I have to stop and reflect for a minute. This was picked on a 12 string… damn, that’s some talent. Something tells me that this older recording was sped up just a little.
